his friends.  The Jade Hand is just part of what Ullric is.  Its definately not the first story in the Companions, and not the last...just somewhere in between.<br><br>Furthermore, I prefer a better fantasy than JUST EverQuest offers.  So some things will be much more realistic, just in the name of roleplaying.  NPCs are not always KoS, mobs that we normally use 12+ people to kill, a single man may fell in pairs or more.  Drakes from Temple of Veeshan are a good example.  A mob that takes a raid party to kill, a paladin may take two on at once, in the name of heroism.<br><br>Likewise, death is much more permanent, and instant.  Our heroes can be, at times, much more vulnerable than they are in game.  There is no zoning or camping out in reality.<br><br>All of that being said, I guess I'd better start?</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <p><HR WIDTH="50%" ALIGN="LEFT"><IMG SRC="http://outside.clanpages.com/podside.jpg" ALIGN="left" HEIGHT=100 WIDTH=100><br><b>Ullric Littleblade</b><br>Assassin of Tides of Valor<br><A HREF="http://www.thesafehouse.org">Ayonae Ro Ring Warden</A><BR><i><A HREF="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=83046">"Speed kills if y'know what I mean."</A></i></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uullric.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ullric</A> at: 11/30/01 6:49:11 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uullric.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ullric</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(11/30/01 7:58:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=57.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Capture.</span><hr size=1> The mountains near Kaladim had grown quiet as the afternoon wore on. Now that the sun was closing on the horizon, the silence was almost complete.  The only disturbance was a pair of travellers, moving at a languid pace among the gorges and valleys.  The two, both mounted, contrasted each other greatly, watched from a distance.<br><br>One moved slowly, almost carefully.  Little more than a vague manling shape under a long charcol cloak with a deep hood covering his bowed head.  He was larger though, than a normal man, and he nearly seemed asleep as he rocked with the motions of the magnificent beast beneath him, its coat nearly the same shade as its rider's cloak.<br><br>The other rider was much smaller, a dwarf in shining golden plate, he rode a white pony, scrambling over rocky slopes and moving in quick bursts, always scanning the area with wary green eyes.<br><br>Eventually, the cloaked man spoke, his voice a deep baritone, though he spoke softly, barely heard above the clatter of steel shod hooves on stone, &quot;Ever vigilant, Paladin.  Even so close to your own home?&quot;<br><br>The pony skidded down a slope as its short rider turned to face the larger, his auburn beard bristling, &quot;When in the company of thieves!&quot;<br><br>The larger man snorted, cutting him off.  He reigned his great mare in, looking up, revealing a handsome, if weary face, framed by brown hair and a beard, and highlighted by midnight blue facepaint in a swirling design skating across his left cheek.  &quot;We are going to have this conversation again?&quot;<br><br>The dwarf groaned, his steed also halting, &quot;Please Brell, no Ullric!  I'll not put up with another minute of your prattle of pillaging in the name of Gods!&quot;<br><br>Ullric smirked, &quot;You are lucky then, friend.  For this is where we part.&quot;<br><br>The dwarf looked around, recognition dawning on his ruddied face, &quot;So it is!  And time is late, so we must part quickly!&quot;<br><br>And they did, the dwarf moving north among the rocky lands, while Ullric headed east, under the eaves of the Faydark.  As they parted, the barbarian raised a hand to his companion, &quot;Fair well, Haak!  And remember, we meet here in two days time!&quot;<br><br><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><center> * * *</center><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br><br>Under the eaves of the ancient forest, twilight came on rider and mount quickly.  The nearly black horse neighed restlessly, eyeing the darkness as it plodded along among the widely spaced trees.  Ullric patted her gracefully arched neck comfortingly, &quot;Be calm, my dear, and have Faith,&quot; He grinned at his own pun, and the horse snorted again, &quot;No harm will come to us in the Faydark.  We are guarded by the Protectors of the Glade.&quot;  The shadows seemed to shift at that moment, punctuating his comment.<br><br>Then the first arrow came.<br><br>Out of the darkness it whistled, its mark deadly.  Only the instincts of Ullric's steed, Faith, saved him, as she bucked suddenly, the arrow narrowly missing his head and striking the tree beyond him, sinking into the bark with a melodic thud.  Ullric shouted in alarm as Faith wheeled, both rider and mount searching for their assailant.  In Ullric's hands now were a shortbow, strung with an arrow nocked.  Faith's reigns lay slack around the horn of his saddle, and he guided her unconsciously with his knees.  Still no one, man or beast revealed themselves.<br><br>More arrows, barely heard as they cut through the air.  Faith sidled to the left, both of the new missles missing by narrow margins as Ullric returned fire into the darkness.  He nocked another arrow, realizing how desperite his fight was.<br><br>Another arrow, he was faster this time. Before this latest shot had even been sighted he loosed his own.  Ullric was rewarded with a thin cry of pain, followed by his own grunt.  Looking down, the barbarian blinked at the arrow shaft protruding from the left side of his ribs.<br><br>More arrows shot from the darkness.  The rogue swayed uneasily in his saddle, the bow clattering from his hands as he grabbed for the saddle horn, trying to keep his balance as Faith danced about.<br><br>Despite her deft maneuvering, two more arrows struck the warhorses' master.  She felt his weight slump against her neck, and she snorted in anger at the darkness, foam frothing from her muzzle as she challenged the unknown attackers.  They replied, lithe humanoid figures garbed in the shades of the forest.  She reared, lashing out with steel shod hooves, and one fell.<br><br>But to her alarm, the mare felt the comforting weight of her master and companion slide from her back.  She wheeled, but was too late, the figures already slipping into the darkness with him.<br><br>Faith stood in the darkness of the Faydark, legs stiff, breathing heavily, rage filling her breast.  Her master was taken, what was she to do? <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uullric.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ullric</A> at: 12/2/01 9:23:37 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uzeezromdraxon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zeezrom Draxon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardfellow</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(11/30/01 2:39:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=57.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Capture.</span><hr size=1> Encore!   <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>~Zee!@#<br>Grand Master of the Sideways Run<br>Proud Elder of Legend of the Jokers<br><img src=http://members.home.net/crux/zeeplaysig.gif></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uullric.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ullric</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Board Veteran</span><br> <font co